<Author>weatherguy92
<Content>If only looking at location and price, this place is great! However, if things like cleanliness, clean drinking water, or noise until late at night bother you, like they did my family of four, DO NOT stay here. On the good side, the location is Fabulous. The recipionist does put on a decent act of friendliness, just don't exhaust it. And the beds were okay. On the bad side. The airconditioning is a joke. It either just didn't work at all, or wasn't worth trying to figure out how to run. In any case it was quite warm and humid in the room. The interior and floor are crying to be refinished. While not filthy, they were by not stretch of the imagaination 'clean'. The sink water was the worst. If it wasn't supposed to be drinkable, it sure didn't say so, but it sure tasted it came straight from the ocean. And to top it off, with the great location comes the great noise from Las Ramblas below, which is all fine and festive until 11pm when you would like to go to sleep. All in all we would never come back to this place, and like I said before, unless all you are concerned about is price and location, I highly recommend you stay away from this place as well. 
