<Author>SylviaGlasgow
<Content>Not Bad Spent 3 nights at the Mur Mar in December, it had its good points but it also had its bad points. First Off i will start with the good points:- The Apartment itsself was good. It has a seperate lounge, kitchen and bedroom so it is basically laid out like a one bedroom flat. The kitchen has all the facilities that you require and our appartment had a balcony which looked over the La Rambla. The location of the appartment is excellent if you want to be right in the heart of everything as it is right on the La Rambla and near to the Harbour.Now for the bad points:-The shower in the bathroom does not stay on the wall so you have to hold the shower over your head which can be a pain when all you want is a quick shower. The apartments themselves were absolutley freezing and didnt have any heating. In the summer i am sure this would be fine but it was 11 degrees outside and even then it was warmer outside than it was in the appartment. There is also a club across the road which comes out at 4am and the noise is unbearable. The shouting and screaming when on for about 3 hrs before it stopped.I would maybe stay at the Mur Mar again if it was in the summer but i would definatley not go back in the winter time again. 
